<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-04-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-04-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4757/8–9.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Riddle</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-18"><hi rend="italic">April 18,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 31.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm herewith
                            department’s telegram received the 11th instance As soon as I could see
                            Baron Meyendorff, the director ad interim of the Russian Eed Cross, I
                            handed him the sum of 9,700 roubles, proceeds of the draft for $5,000 as
                            shown by the inclosed memorandum of the St. Petersburg Commercial Joint
                            Stock Bank. I also inclose the receipt for the sum mentioned of the
                            Russian Red Cross with an English translation.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. W. Riddle.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>